text: Tertullian Pyne was an Anglican priest in England during the 16th century.The History and Antiquities of the County of Norfolk, M. Booth (ed), Norwich, J. Crouse, 1781. Pyne was born in Devon and educated at St John's College, Oxford.Alumni Oxonienses 1500-1714, Pritchard-Pyx He held the living at Swanscombe and was appointed Archdeacon of Sudbury in 1593. == References == Category:Alumni of St John's College, Oxford Category:Archdeacons of Sudbury Category:Clergy from Devon Category:16th-century English Anglican priests
title: Tertullian Pyne
